    {
      "id": "7e0bb0aaa33935db2ef39ea3d1c321c141c7477b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-28 10:06:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 8: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\ncan you comment on how you deal with LinkEA and orphans?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 8
    },
    {
      "id": "1221167e2bb666dd585cc19c201c4e7b44041b18",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-05-28 10:52:48.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 8:\n\n> Alex Zhuravlev\t\t6:06 PM\n> Patch Set 8: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n> can you comment on how you deal with LinkEA and orphans?\n\nFirstly, the LFSCK uses namespace-based directory traversal to perform linkEA consistency check/repair. It only scans the /ROOT and its descendants. So the objects under /PENDING will be skipped.\n\nIf the object becomes orphan just during the LFSCK processing such object, then linkEA verification policy will guarantee the consistency. When the LFSCK update the object linkEA (add/del/modify), it will lock (osd_write_lock) the target object, then the LFSCK will perform lookup under its current parent. If the target object has become orphan, then the lookup will return -ENOENT, and then the LFSCK knows that related linkEA is redundant. Otherwise, before the LFSCK unlock the target object, nobody can make the target object as orphan.\n\nAbove processing is based on local MDT, if DNE involved, then related object will be skipped. We will handle those cases in LFSCK phase III.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 8
    },
    {
      "id": "14ff524ee51f03d84dd3cf91024ce21e7bc6c3dd",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-28 10:55:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 8:\n\nok, thanks\n\n> Above processing is based on local MDT, if DNE involved, then related object will be skipped. We will handle those cases in LFSCK phase III.\n\nthe iterator must not return remote objects.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 8
    },
    {
      "id": "09d3ab40dcde935251e001c634651db7a56de4a4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-05-28 11:51:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 8:\n\n> the iterator must not return remote objects.\n\nThe target object can be remote, or its parent can be remote.\n\nFor low layer iterator, it may needs to return remote object (or its fid), because the iterator is shared by all the LFSCK components. And the LFSCK needs to process DNE inconsistency check/repair (in phase III).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 8
    },
    {
      "id": "d9a5b157ab2dd85fe219ef85d23478ec55ee25b4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-28 11:53:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 8:\n\n> The target object can be remote, or its parent can be remote.\n\nthis is fine\n\n> For low layer iterator, it may needs to return remote object (or its fid), because the iterator is shared by all the LFSCK components. \n\nthis is not. the iterator can return only object this OSD stores.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 8
    },
    {
      "id": "74c292da56db468aa5ccefe3b4fc93f7054e3b55",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-05-28 12:00:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 8:\n\n> this is not. the iterator can return only object this OSD stores.\n\nYes, the otable-based iteration will not return remote object.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 8
    },
    {
      "id": "ddc18ab5587ba55aa1c904da5927dde27b31730f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-28 23:00:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 8: Looks good to me, approved\n\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 8
    },
